</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Techcrunch/~4/320007744" height="1" width="1"/>";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1214429094;}i:15;a:9:{s:5:"title";s:52:"TripSay Rolls Out Improvements, Expands Private Beta";s:4:"link";s:55:"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Techcrunch/~3/320004543/";s:11:"description";s:371:"TripSay, the site that uses social recommendations to guide users through the plethora of travel information on the web, has introduced a number of new features that it hopes will improve the site&#8217;s accuracy and encourage collaboration. The site now features leaderboards that should encourage users to become &#8220;experts&#8221; in their region, which will [...]";s:4:"guid";s:34:"http://www.techcrunch.com/?p=19325";s:7:"pubdate";s:29:"Wed, 25 Jun 2008 13:56:26 PDT";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:2481:"<p><a rel="nofollow"><img src="http://www.techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/06/tripsaylogo.png" class="shot2"/></a></p>
<p><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://www.tripsay.com">TripSay</a>, the site that <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://www.techcrunch.com/2008/04/14/tripsay-lets-you-discover-the-world-with-a-little-help-from-your-friends-beta-invites/">uses social recommendations</a> to guide users through the plethora of travel information on the web, has introduced a number of new features that it hopes will improve the site&#8217;s accuracy and encourage collaboration. </p>
<p>The site now features leaderboards that should encourage users to become &#8220;experts&#8221; in their region, which will be essential if it hopes to generate worthwhile content. Users now also can create groups, where they&#8217;ll be able share information and travel plans with trusted friends.</p>
<p>In conjunction with these new features, TripSay is expanding its private beta; TechCrunch readers can grab one of 500 invites by emailing <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="mailto: info@tripsay.com?subject=TechCrunch">info@tripsay.com</a>. TripSay competes with countless other travel sites, but tries to differentiate itself by offering fewer, but more targeted, recommendations.</p>
<p><strong><em>Crunch Network</em></strong>: <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://www.crunchboard.com">CrunchBoard</a><em> </em>because it&#8217;s time for you to find a new Job2.0</p> <p><a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~a/Techcrunch?a=pakFVe"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~a/Techcrunch?i=pakFVe" border="0"></a></p><div class="feedflare">
