re appropriate<br> management of chemical substances and address a broad range of other environmental issues.<br> Through these initiatives, Sony is striving to achieve an absolute reduction in greenhouse gas<br> emissions, specifically a 7% or greater reduction in CO2 emissions by FY2010 compared to the<br> level of FY2000.</p> <p>Financial Strategies for the Mid-Term</p> <p>In order to generate funds to continue to grow and innovate, Sony has identified a 5 percent<br> operating margin as a baseline of profitability. Sony is also establishing return on investment<br> capital as a fundamental framework for evaluating capital investments and potential acquisitions<br> across the Sony Group to ensure the optimum use of resources. Our targeted investment (an<br> aggregate of 1.8 trillion yen by the end of FY2010) will put Sony in a position to drive further<br> growth and innovation over the next three years and beyond. Sony will also target an annual<br> return on equity of 10% by FY2010. Going forward, we will work to deliver a stable, high level of<br> profitability while enhancing shareholder value.</p> <p>The business environment in which Sony operates is changing rapidly and, with the advance in<br> digital technology and broadband networks, technological innovation is moving at a pace never<br> experienced before. In order to be a leading company in the digital age, Sony aims to leverage its<br> unique advantage of producing both hardware and content, continuing to offer cutting-edge<br> products together with superior content and services to meet the needs and expectations of our<br> customers.</p> </blockquote> <p>[<a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://www.sony.net/SonyInfo/News/Press/200806/08-080E/">Sony</a> and <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://66.102.9.104/translate_c?hl=en&sl=ja&u=http://www.watch.impress.co.jp/av/docs/20080626/sony1.htm">Impress</a>]</p> <br style="clear:both;"/> <img alt="" style="border:0;height:1px;width:1px;" b